  "elapsed_s": 83.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had-- we had some information.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Also, at age 12, I am talking about.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was aware of what was going on in the country, and what was going on with the Jews, and what was going on with my parents' livelihood.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Very much aware of it, and it was disturbing for me as a child.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I also had some information from-- firsthand information about what goes on in other countries.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the neighboring country-- neighboring country on the north from Hungary, Czechoslovakia, we had one classmate who joined us at the age 12.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a big thing if somebody came from another school, because usually, who started are the ones who finish, and not too many changes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But this classmate of mine, unfortunately, I know for sure that he didn't survive, [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Yanosh ?] Jan Popper, P-O-P-P-E-R, a very wonderful young man who came from Czechoslovakia, where his parents gave up everything, because anti-Semitic laws and anti-Semitic atrocities were so rampant and so bad that they found and thought that it's safer to move to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's what he said.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why his parents came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I also had a classmate who joined at about the same time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His name is Pfeiffer-- I can't remember right now the first name-- who came from Austria for the same reasons, that they found and though that they better have a chance to survive in Hungary than--",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--their own country where they were born and raised.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I would be able only to tell that it was because Jewish life was getting very untolerable for them over there and livelihood and for his parents' livelihood was cut away.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
